  <text>
    <body>
      <p>Bruno's Weekly was the representative journal of the
      Greenwich Village modernists, exclusively featuring the poetry,
      stories, and gossip of local writers. It ran for little more
      than one year (from July 1915 to December 1916) in conjunction
      with Guido Bruno's other short-lived publications Greenwich
      Village (1915), Bruno's Chap Books (1915-1916), Bruno's (1917),
      and Bruno's Bohemia (1918). Selected Contributors: Guido Bruno,
      Djuna Barnes, Alfred Kreymborg, Marianne Moore, Vincent
      Starrett, Ford Madox Hueffer.</p>
